"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421298","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>An independent assessment of the potential economic impact of proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership on the UK was carried out by the Centre for Economic Policy Research (CEPR). The CEPR analysis includes an assessment of the impact on twenty broad sectors of the economy, with estimated impacts on output, trade and shifts in employment. This can be found on the GOV.UK website.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-28T14:50:52.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421298/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421298/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment the Government has made of the potential economic and employment effects of the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership on the (a) food and farming, (b) energy, (c) financial services, (d) technology, (e) textiles and (f) shipbuilding sectors.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","11960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421299","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>An independent assessment of the potential economic impact of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) on the UK as a whole was carried out for the Government by the Centre for Economic Policy Research (CEPR). This assessment demonstrated that TTIP offers an enormous economic benefit: in growth, exports and high quality jobs, worth up to £10 billion a year.</p><p>We are currently considering undertaking further research into effects of TTIP in each of the UK regions.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","11962","2015-10-28T17:49:14.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421299/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421299/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment the Government has made of the potential economic and employment effects of the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership in each of the constituent parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","11961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421300","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>An independent assessment of the potential economic impact of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) on the UK as a whole was carried out for the Government by the Centre for Economic Policy Research (CEPR). This assessment demonstrated that TTIP offers an enormous economic benefit: in growth, exports and high quality jobs, worth up to £10 billion a year.</p><p>We are currently considering undertaking further research into effects of TTIP in each of the UK regions.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","11961","2015-10-28T17:49:14.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421300/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421300/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will assess the potential economic and employment effects of the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership in each of the constituent parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","11962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421301","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-21","<p>Statistics on English domiciled applicants awarded Maintenance Grants for study at UK providers are published annually by the Student Loans Company (SLC) in the Statistical First Release ‘<em>Student Support for Higher Education in England</em>’.</p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx</a></p><p>The best available indication of the number of students likely to be affected is the actual number of grant recipients in 2013/14.</p><p>The number of Maintenance Grants awarded to English domiciled applicants from (a) Manchester, Withington constituency and (b) studying at Manchester University and Manchester Metropolitan University in the academic year 2013/14 has been provided in the table.</p><p><strong>Maintenance Grants<sup>(1) </sup>awarded<sup>(2)</sup> to English applicants</strong></p><p><strong>Academic year 2013/14</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong></strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of awarded applicants (3)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Constituency<sup>(4)</sup></strong></p></td><td><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manchester, Withington</p></td><td><p>1,400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Higher Education Provider</strong></p></td><td><p><strong></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manchester Metropolitan University</p></td><td><p>14,090</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>University of Manchester</p></td><td><p>7,300</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Student Loans Company</p><p>(1) Figures include Special Support Grants</p><p>(2) Awards do not necessarily translate into payments. An awarded applicant will only receive payments once SLC have received confirmation from the student’s provider that the student has been registered on the course.</p><p>(3) Numbers are rounded to the nearest 10. Totals may not add to the sum of the components due to rounding.</p><p>(4) Constituency is derived from the home address of the student as stated on application for student finance.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-21T14:51:20.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421301/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421301/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Students: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of how many students (a) from Manchester, Withington constituency and (b) studying at Manchester University and Manchester Metropolitan University will be affected by the removal of maintenance loans.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","11865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421302","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<br /><p>The Department is introducing the National Living Wage in April 2016, which will be the legal minimum wage for those over 25. It will be set at £7.20 per hour, and the Low Pay Commission will advise on the increases each year towards the ambition that it reaches 60% of median earnings by 2020.</p><br /><p>The Office of Budget Responsibility estimates that by 2020 it will benefit 2.7 million workers directly and up to a total of 6 million workers could see a pay rise as a result of a ripple effect up the earnings distribution. The Government also supports those employers who can afford to pay more.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-20T14:45:39.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421302/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421302/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to increase the proportion of people whose earnings are above the living wage.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","11824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421303","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-22","<p>The objectives for the recent sale of Royal Mail shares, as set out in the Secretary of State’s report to Parliament on 8 June 2015 (Royal Mail: Sale of Shares), included delivering a “financial outcome for the tax payer that represents overall value for money”.</p><p>To achieve this, the Department was supported by advice from its independent financial adviser, Rothschild, on the fair value of the company. Rothschild conducted a wide ranging analysis of the value of Royal Mail. The price per share achieved in the recent sale realised value for money for the tax payer.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-22T15:48:52.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421303/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421303/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to ensure maximum financial benefit to the public purse from the sale of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421304","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>Advice and guidance on business risk is provided via the online Overseas Business Risks guides.</p><p>These are a joint UK Trade &amp; Investment and FCO resource and provide information for businesses on the potential risks of trading in specific countries. Guides cover political and economic risks, human rights issues, bribery, terrorism, criminal activity, and intellectual property.</p><p>The information for the Occupied Palestinian Territories can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/overseas-business-risk-palestinian-territories" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/overseas-business-risk-palestinian-territories</a></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-28T14:52:46.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421304/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421304/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Overseas Trade: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what (a) advice and (b) guidance his Department gives on the risks of (i) investment in and (ii) business with Israeli settlements in Occupied Palestinian territory.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","11818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421305","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>Targets have not been set for apprenticeships at specific levels.</p><br /><p>New apprenticeships standards are being designed by groups of employers as part of our reforms, through the Trailblazers, to meet their needs. These standards reflect the skills, knowledge and behaviours at whatever level is required to undertake the chosen occupation competently and to operate confidently within the sector.</p><br /><p>We will continue to grow apprenticeships at Higher (Level 4) and Degree levels. These are widening access to the professions and providing the higher level technical skills that employers need to improve productivity and give young people an equally valid career route as going to university.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-20T14:46:56.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421305/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421305/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many of his Department's target of three million apprenticeship starts by 2020 he expects to be at Level 3 and above.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","11924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421306","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Student Loans Company (SLC) administers student support for the UK Government and Devolved Administrations. Information on the number of borrowers is published annually by the SLC in the Statistical First Release ‘<em>Student Loans in England: FY 2014-15</em>’.</p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/student-loans-debt-and-repayment/england.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/student-loans-debt-and-repayment/england.aspx</a></p><br /><p>At the end of the financial year 2014-15, there were 1,640 borrowers on post-2012 student loan arrangements who had been domiciled in Hove when they applied for financial support.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T15:30:41.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421306/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421306/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-14","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of how many Hove residents who have taken out student loans since 2012 will be affected by proposals to freeze the repayment threshold of the loans at £21,000.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","11923"
