"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421450","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-21","<p>I refer the hon member to the Secretary of State’s statement of 13 October 2015. As has been the practice with successive administrations, details of internal discussions are not normally disclosed. We have no plans to undertake an impact assessment.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","11806","2015-10-21T10:12:46.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421450/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421450/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Prisons: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will publish the review which led the Government to decide not to proceed with a prisons training contract with Saudi Arabia.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","11956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421451","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-21","<p>It would incur disproportionate cost to obtain this information.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-21T15:44:21.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421451/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421451/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Ministry of Justice: Legal Opinion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department spent on external legal advice not from Queen's Counsel since 7 May 2010.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","11957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421452","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-21","<p>Charities and the voluntary sector have long played an important role in rehabilitating offenders and continue to do so under the Government’s reforms to rehabilitation services. Under the Transforming Rehabilitation reforms, we opened up the market in order to get the best out of the public, private and third sectors. 19 out of the 21 CRCs are being run with assistance from staff mutual or VCSE, and all contracted probation providers have included VCSE organisations in their supply chains.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-21T09:38:35.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421452/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421452/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps Community Rehabilitation Companies are taking to engage with local charities to prevent prisoners from reoffending.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","11973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421453","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-22","<p>The release of prisoners serving indeterminate sentences of imprisonment for public protection (IPP) is a matter for the independent Parole Board. The Parole Board directs the release of IPP prisoners on licence who have completed their minimum period of imprisonment (tariff), where the Board is satisfied that those prisoners may be effectively managed in the community.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-22T16:40:00.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421453/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421453/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress his Department is making in arranging for the release of prisoners sentenced to imprisonment for public protection.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","11905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454","Ministry of Justice","true","2015-10-22","<p>As the Secretary of State stated to the House on 8 September, we have been made aware of widespread concern about the operation of the Criminal Courts Charge, but it is important to stress that the Charge is levied or taken from the offender only after other <ins class="ministerial">impositions</ins><del class="ministerial">fines</del> have been paid. It is important to note that statutory protections are in place so that the payment of the Charge in due course should be linked to the offender's means. Within the Bill there was a duty placed on the Lord Chancellor to carry out a review of the Criminal Courts Charge, three years after the implementation of the Charge.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-22T16:50:53.663Z","2015-10-23T11:04:35.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454/answer","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454/answer/previousversion/25299","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421454/answer/previousversion/25299",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Criminal Proceedings: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what his policy is on the Criminal Court Charge.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","11877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421455","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-22","<p>The Secretary of State for Justice has had no discussions on the recruitment processes for vacancies in the College of Arms and has no responsibility for such.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-22T08:44:59.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421455/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421455/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","College of Arms: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent discussions he has had on recruitment processes for vacancies in the College of Arms.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","11803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421456","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-21","<p>Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs), including Staffordshire and West Midlands CRC, set out an agreed operating model within their bids during the Transforming Rehabilitation competition. These bids were rigorously scrutinised before contracts were awarded. A thorough evaluation process was undertaken to assess the operational viability of the bids in the wider context of public protection and reducing reoffending.</p><br /><p>All CRCs are contractually required to maintain a professional and appropriately skilled workforce to deliver the services set out in their contracts. The MoJ closely monitors the performance of CRCs, in line with government standards, to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending and deliver value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-21T09:46:21.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421456/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421456/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-14","Staffordshire and West Midlands Community Rehabilitation Company: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will make representations to Staffordshire and West Midlands Rehabilitation Company on ensuring jobs are not lost by the planned transfer of responsibilities for probation service administration staff to Derby.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","11814"
