"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420919","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>The involvement of the Irish Government in cross-party talks is in accordance with the established three-stranded approach to Northern Ireland affairs and the 1998 Belfast Agreement. A commitment always to uphold the three-stranded approach was also contained in the Government’s Northern Ireland manifesto at the General Election.</p><br />",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2015-10-19T11:15:02.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420919/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420919/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-10-13","Northern Ireland Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Dunlop on 18 September (HL2210), whether they can confirm that the government of the Republic of Ireland has not had representatives at any discussions other than those allowed by the 1998 Belfast Agreement.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420920","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-21","<p>Helping disabled people to live independently in their own homes for longer through adaptations remains a key priority for this Government. The Government will have invested just over a billion pounds into the Disabled Facilities Grant between 2011-12 and 2015-16. This has delivered around 200,000 adaptations to the homes of disabled people. Future funding for the Disabled Facilities Grant is a matter for the Spending Review.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL2607","2015-10-21T15:10:48.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420920/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420920/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-13","Disabled Facilities Grants","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what will be the total amount available under the Disability Facilities Grant fund in 2016–17.","false","Biography information for Baroness Greengross",,"Baroness Greengross","HL2606"
