"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420930","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-16","<p>My Rt hon Friends the Secretaries of State for Business, Innovation and Skills and Transport have jointly engaged in an exchange of correspondence with Paul Willis, Head of Volkswagen (VW) UK on VW’s plans for addressing consumer concerns over the fitting of defeat devices fitted to VW branded vehicles in the UK (including Northern Ireland). Both Ministers have urged VW UK to complete the refit/redress process as quickly as possible.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-16T13:39:11.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420930/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420930/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-13","Cars: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with Volkswagen and Renault on the recall of cars in Northern Ireland aged one to five years for refitting new computer and brake systems; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","11752"
