"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146","Home Office","false","2015-10-21","<p>National standards for training police officers in the deployment of stinger devices is an operational matter for individual police Chief Officers drawing on the police’s own Authorised Professional Practice of England and Wales Police, developed by the College of Policing.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-21T15:46:41.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146/answer/previousversion/23866","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421146/answer/previousversion/23866",,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-13","Police: Stun Guns","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the national standards are for the training and guidance of police officers in deploying stinger devices.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","11554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421147","Home Office","false","2015-10-26","<p>The Home Office is working with all interested parties to confirm the most efficient and effective way to enable mothers’ names to be recorded on marriage certificates.</p><p>Achieving this is likely to require additional funding and changes to legislation, IT systems and administrative processes.</p><p>The Government will confirm a timetable for the introduction of the changes in due course.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-26T17:28:58.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421147/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421147/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-13","Marriage Certificates: Mothers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the reasons are for the time taken to change regulations to allow mothers' names to be recorded on marriage certificates; what timetable is in place for that change to be made; whether she has made an assessment of the feasibility of allowing that change to be phased in as marriage registers are replaced; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","11550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421148","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>The cost of replacing the registers is being assessed in conjunction with our work to determine the most efficient and effective way to enable mothers’ names to be recorded on marriage certificates.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-22T15:33:37.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421148/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421148/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-13","Marriage Certificates: Mothers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an estimate of the potential (a) total and (b) average cost per register of allowing mothers names to be recorded on marriage certificates.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","11551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421149","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>The information requested is shown in the attached table.</p><br /><p>The latest quarterly Home Office immigration statistics on entry clearance visas are published in ‘Immigration Statistics, April-June 2015’, available from the Library of the House and from the Home Office website at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-statistics</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-22T16:32:40.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421149/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421149/answer","Table for PQ 11527.xlsx","Table for PQ 11527.xlsx","Transit visa applications Syrian Nationals","Transit visa applications Syrian Nationals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421149/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-13","Visas: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many transit visas for Syrian nationals have been (a) granted and (b) refused in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","11527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421150","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-18","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government, the Home Office and the Department of Health led joint consultation ‘Enabling closer working between the Emergency Services’ has made clear that should Police and Crime Commissioners assume responsibility for fire and rescue services, the important distinction between operational policing and firefighting will be maintained. The consultation did not propose to change the current rules around industrial action.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-11-18T15:45:05.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421150/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421150/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-13","Fire Services: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Department's consultation, Enabling closer working between the Emergency Services, whether firefighters employed by police and crime commissioners will retain the right to take part in industrial action; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421151","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>There are no plans for a specific review of the administrative handling of immigration applications. UKVI is, however, committed to the principles of continuous improvement and to applying these to ensure processes are efficient and effective.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-22T16:35:33.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421151/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421151/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-13","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will conduct a review into the efficiency and effectiveness of administrative handling of cases.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","11574"
